docs.abstract: Lawyers for the Justice Department and Google as well as the judge in a monthslong trial have invoked the landmark case against Microsoft from the 1990s.

docs.lead_paragraph: Antitrust trials are full of long stretches of detailed, often tedious testimony punctuated by telling moments. In the two-month Google antitrust trial that is nearing its conclusion, one of those moments came in a brief exchange in October.

headline.main: How Microsoft’s Legal Legacy Shapes the Antitrust Case Against Google
headline.print_headline: Microsoft Case’s Legacy Shapes a Google Trial

docs.abstract: It is hard to see the past few days as anything but a big loss for the A.I. company.

docs.lead_paragraph: For a while this weekend, it looked as if Sam Altman might return as a conquering hero to OpenAI, the company whose board had fired him as chief executive on Friday.

headline.main: The Winners and Losers of OpenAI’s Wild Weekend
headline.print_headline: A Chief Was Ousted, But Who Won the Day?

docs.abstract: Mr. Altman was forced out of the artificial intelligence start-up on Friday, leading to an outcry from his supporters and the company’s investors.

docs.lead_paragraph: Sam Altman and Greg Brockman, two top executives at OpenAI who left the company after a dramatic board meeting on Friday, are talking again with board members about returning to the artificial intelligence start-up, two people with knowledge of the matter said.

headline.main: Sam Altman Is Said to Be Discussing Return to OpenAI With Company’s Board
